#: ../../../release/1.8.1-notes.rst:91
msgid ""
"The utility function npy_PyFile_Dup and npy_PyFile_DupClose are broken by "
"the internal buffering python 3 applies to its file objects. To fix this two "
"new functions npy_PyFile_Dup2 and npy_PyFile_DupClose2 are declared in "
"npy_3kcompat.h and the old functions are deprecated. Due to the fragile "
"nature of these functions it is recommended to instead use the python API "
"when possible."
msgstr ""
